# Person

## Summary
Person is the shared base card for people in the Table Seating Planner package. It holds a `fullName` string, a `photo` image source, and a computed `photoURL` derived from that photo; its `title` falls back to "Unnamed Person" when the name is blank. Guest and Host both extend Person, inheriting these identity fields plus the avatar-row embedded view. The package ships no standalone Person instances — it exists to be subclassed.

## Import
```js
import { Person } from '../person';
```

## Usage
Person is a card, so link to it (or, more commonly, extend it the way Guest and Host do):

```js
import { CardDef, field, linksTo } from 'https://cardstack.com/base/card-api';
import { Person } from '../person';

export class ContactCard extends CardDef {
  @field contact = linksTo(Person);
}
```

## Template Usage
```handlebars
<@fields.contact @format='embedded' />
```
Renders the person as a compact row with a photo (or initials) avatar and their name.
